<title>MEXICO: Apasco dividend, buyback reserve approved.</title>
<headline>Apasco dividend, buyback reserve approved.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-04-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexican cement company Apasco said its shareholders on Thursday approved a one peso per share dividend, payable from April 30, and the creation of a $350 million peso reserve to buy back shares.</p>
<p>In a statement, it said the measures were approved at a shareholders meeting. The dividend represents 278 million pesos, and will be paid for every share in circulation.</p>
<p>The buyback reserve will cover up to three percent of Apasco's share capital.</p>
<p>((--Henry Tricks, Mexico City newsroom +525 728 9560))</p>
